title: Mother's Day
desc: Celebrate and honor mothers.
content: Mother's Day is a day to show appreciation for mothers and mother figures. It is celebrated with gifts, meals, and gestures of love to honor their contributions and sacrifices.

title: Father's Day
desc: Celebrate and honor fathers.
content: Father's Day is a time to recognize the hard work and love of fathers. Celebrate with gifts, heartfelt messages, and activities that highlight the importance of fatherhood.

title: St. Patrick's Day
desc: Celebrate Irish culture with parades and green attire.
content: St. Patrick's Day is a celebration of Irish heritage, featuring parades, music, and people wearing green. It's a time to enjoy Irish food and beverages and share in the spirit of the day.

title: Labor Day
desc: A day to honor the American labor movement.
content: Labor Day celebrates the contributions of American workers and the labor movement. It's a time to relax, enjoy time with family, and appreciate the workforce's efforts.

title: Columbus Day
desc: A day to commemorate Christopher Columbus' arrival in the Americas.
content: Columbus Day marks the landing of Christopher Columbus in the Americas. It's a day to reflect on exploration, history, and the diverse cultures that shape the world today.

title: International Women's Day
desc: Celebrate the achievements of women worldwide.
content: International Women's Day honors the social, economic, cultural, and political achievements of women. It's a day to advocate for gender equality and celebrate women's contributions globally.

title: Summer Solstice
desc: Celebrate the longest day of the year.
content: The Summer Solstice marks the longest day of the year and the official start of summer. It's a time to enjoy outdoor activities, festivals, and celebrate the warmth of the season.

title: New Year's Day
desc: The first day of the year, a time for new beginnings.
content: New Year's Day marks the start of a new year and offers a fresh beginning. It's a time for reflection on the past year and setting new goals for the year ahead.

title: Memorial Day
desc: Honor the fallen heroes of the U.S. military.
content: Memorial Day is a day to remember and honor those who have given their lives for the country. It is often marked with ceremonies, parades, and the decoration of veterans' graves.

title: World Photography Day
desc: Celebrate the art of photography.
content: World Photography Day celebrates the art of photography, encouraging people to capture moments and preserve memories. It's a day to appreciate the power of visual storytelling.

title: Bastille Day
desc: Celebrate French Revolution and the values of liberty and equality.
content: Bastille Day marks the anniversary of the French Revolution, commemorating the storming of the Bastille. It's a celebration of liberty, equality, and fraternity with fireworks and parades.

title: Lincoln's Birthday
desc: Celebrate the birthday of Abraham Lincoln.
content: Lincoln's Birthday honors the life and legacy of the 16th President of the United States. It's a day to reflect on his contributions to the nation's growth and ideals.

title: New Year's Eve Party
desc: Celebrate the upcoming year with an exciting party.
content: New Year's Eve Party is a celebration of the year's end, filled with live music, dancing, and a countdown to the new year. It's an exciting way to bid farewell to the old year and welcome the new.

title: International Youth Day
desc: Celebrate the youth and their contributions.
content: International Youth Day celebrates the role of young people in shaping society. It encourages youth participation and highlights their contributions in various fields.

title: International Day of Peace
desc: Promote peace and non-violence.
content: International Day of Peace is dedicated to strengthening the ideals of peace, non-violence, and harmony across the globe. It encourages individuals to participate in activities that promote understanding and cooperation.

title: Christmas Eve
desc: A night of joy and anticipation for Christmas Day.
content: Christmas Eve is a time for reflection and preparation for the big day ahead. It's a time to gather with family, enjoy festive meals, and anticipate the arrival of Christmas.

title: Halloween Costume Contest
desc: Show off your spooky and creative costumes.
content: The Halloween Costume Contest is a fun event where participants show off their most creative and spooky costumes. It's a chance to compete for prizes and celebrate Halloween in style.
